The photo-Fenton process was optimized as follows, by maintaining fixed conditions of temperature = 298 K, agitation 350 rpm and t = 30 min:
Performance of H2O2 variation (2–16 mM), pH 3.0, [Fe2+] = 0.15 mM, [AR88] = 50 mg L−1 radiation UV-A (365 nm), IUV = 32.7 W m−2;
Performance of Fe2+ variation (0.05−0.20 mM), pH 3.0, [H2O2] = 4 mM, [AR88] = 50 mg L−1adiation UV-A (365 nm), IUV = 32.7 W m−2;
Performance of NTA variation (0.05–0.20 mM), pH 3.0, [H2O2] = 4 mM, [Fe2+] = 0.15 mM, [AR88] = 50 mg L−1radiation UV-A (365 nm), IUV = 32.7 W m−2;
Performance of [AR88] variation (25–100 mg L−1), pH 3.0, [H2O2] = 4 mM, [Fe2+] = 0.15 mM, [NTA] = 0.10 mM, radiation UV-A (365 nm), IUV = 32.7 W m−2;
Performance of pH variation (3.0–7.0), [H2O2] = 4 mM, [Fe2+] = 0.15 mM, [NTA] = 0.10 mM, [AR88] = 50 mg L−1 radiation UV-A (365 nm), IUV = 32.7 W m−2;
Performance of irradiance power variation (IUV = 0 – 32.7 W m−2), pH 3.0, [H2O2] = 4 mM, [Fe2+] = 0.15 mM, [NTA] = 0.10 mM, [AR88] = 50 mg L−1 radiation UV-A (365 nm).

